# Reusable Prompt Templates

Copy, fill the blanks, paste into your AI assistant.

## New module, full stack

```
Create a new {Module} module following Laravel Module Maker conventions.

Entities: {Entity1}, {Entity2}.
For each entity: model with fields ({field:type, ...}), migration, service,
controller, API resource, Store/Update form requests, factory, seeder.

Constraints:
- Scaffold everything with jw:* generators (run_generator MCP tool); never create files by hand.
- Follow .ai/ai-rules.md. Do not create files outside {{ modulesPath }}/{Module}.
- Populate $fillable, write migration columns, validation rules, and resource fields.
- Write feature tests for the CRUD endpoints and run {{ testCommand }}.
```

## Add an endpoint to an existing module

```
In the {Module} module, add {description of endpoint}.

Constraints:
- Inspect the module first (module_structure tool) and extend the existing
  {Entity}Service — do not create a parallel service.
- Route goes in {Module}/Routes/api.php; validation in a FormRequest;
  output through {Entity}Resource.
- Add a feature test; run {{ testCommand }}.
```

## Add a background process

```
In the {Module} module, create a queued job {JobName} that {behavior},
triggered by a {EntityEvent} event.

Constraints:
- jw:make-job, jw:make-event, jw:make-listener — all with --module={Module}.
- Wire the listener to the event in the module ServiceProvider.
- Test the listener dispatches the job.
```

## Review my changes

```
Review the diff against .ai/ai-rules.md and .ai/conventions.md.
Flag: hand-created files that should have used generators, logic in
controllers that belongs in services, missing FormRequests/Resources,
namespace violations, missing $fillable entries, missing tests.
```
